      "writtenOn": "2018-05-19T02:46:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, it can\u0027t be test_helpers.go because then Go would start linking testing packages into non-test binaries that import \u0027interpreter\u0027. For example, just a fact of importing \"testing\" package registers a ton of CLI flags in the default flagset, we don\u0027t want them to appear in non-test binaries.\n\nThus test helpers should live in *_test.go.\n\nI\u0027ve added a test right here, it is not a big deal.",
      "parentUuid": "ed4aec48_a26d90b0",
